	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 6456-39 (120)"/>
			<p>So far one of the principal difficulties for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> wishing to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">flee</term> the perils
				of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName> was that the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_turkish">Turkish</term> Legation here was not empowered to give a transit visa unless the applicant
				could show a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1146" type="subject">visa</term> for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName> or <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/163843/syrian-arab-republic.html">Syria</placeName> which the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_british">British</term> have not given us authority to grant, and which is not accorded to residents
				of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-237" type="subject">enemy</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1031" type="subject">occupied countries</term> such as <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName>.</p>
			<p>I was therefore struck yesterday when my <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_turkish">Turkish</term> colleague called to say that he had
				strongly urged by telegram upon his <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-1374">Government</orgName> the
				desirability of conferring with the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_british">British</term>, and, out of courtesy, with the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_french">French</term>, to see whether there was not some way to arrange temporary lodgings in barracks
				in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/163843/syrian-arab-republic.html">Syria</placeName> or <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName> for the unfortunate <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> still left in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Romania</placeName>. [...]</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-39 (121)"/>
			<p>I am wholly in accord with his proposal which, if adopted, might <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-214"
					type="subject">save</term> many innocent lives and spare extreme human suffering. I have no illusions, however, that the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Romanians</term> will ever let these <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">poor people</term> out of their clutches with more
				than the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> on their backs.</p>
